  • Constructor Details

    • Customer

      public Customer()

    • Customer

      public Customer​(java.lang.String custname, java.lang.String custcity, java.lang.String workingarea, java.lang.String custcountry, java.lang.String grade, double openingamt, double receiveamt, double paymentamt, double outstandingamt, java.lang.String phone, Agent agent)
      Given the params, create a new customer object.

      custcode is autogenerated.

      Parameters:
      custname - The name (String) of the customer.
      custcity - The city (String) of the customer.
      workingarea - The workingarea, geographical location, (String) of the customer.
      custcountry - The country (String) of the customer.
      grade - The grade (String) of the customer.
      openingamt - The openingamt (double) of the customer's account.
      receiveamt - The amount received (double) on the customer's account.
      paymentamt - The payment amount (double) on the customer's account.
      outstandingamt - The amount outstanding (double) on the customer's account.
      phone - The phone number (String) of the agent.
      agent - The agent record associated with this customer. orders are added outside of this constructor.
